# AttenTrack — Full-Stack Digital Wellbeing Analytics

**Stack**: React + Vite | Express.js | MySQL (Sequelize ORM)

Build a full-stack app from the FE wireframe designs. Analyzes screen-time data and provides productivity/attention insights with distraction detection.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> The existing `FE/` folder is preserved as reference. New code goes in `client/` + `server/`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **MySQL**: `user=root`, `password=34691218`, `database=attentrack`. Tables auto-created via `sequelize.sync()`.

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **New Feature: Distracting Apps Detection** — Since this is a web app (not a native desktop agent), detection works as follows:
> - Users **manually add** apps/websites to their personal distraction list (like a blocklist)
> - When screen-time data is imported (CSV/manual), entries are **auto-flagged** as "distracting" if they match the user's list
> - A **browser activity tracker** component periodically logs the active browser tab URL and matches against the list (using `document.visibilityState` + `document.title`)
> - Each user has their own **isolated** distraction list, tasks, reports, and analytics (all tables have `userId` foreign key)

---

## Proposed Changes

### Backend — Models (`server/models/`)

| Model | Key Columns | Purpose |
|-------|-------------|---------|
| **User** | id, email, password(hashed), name | Auth |
| **ScreenTimeEntry** | id, **userId**(FK), app, category, date, usageMinutes, notifications, timesOpened, **isDistracting**(bool) | Usage data, auto-flagged |
| **DistractingApp** ⭐NEW | id, **userId**(FK), appName, type(app/website), url, addedAt | Per-user distraction list |
| **UserTask** ⭐NEW | id, **userId**(FK), title, description, estimatedMinutes, deadline, status, **distractionMinutes**, **completionPercent** | Task tracking + distraction impact |
| **Alert** | id, **userId**(FK), name, triggerType, appOrCategory, thresholdMinutes, active, notificationMethod | Usage alerts |
| **Settings** | id, **userId**(FK), productiveStart, productiveEnd, hourlyRate, dailyGoalMinutes, timezone | Config |
| **Report** | id, **userId**(FK), type, dateFrom, dateTo, format, sections(JSON), filePath | Generated reports |

> Every table is scoped by `userId` — users never see each other's data.

### Backend — Routes (`server/routes/`)

| Route File | Endpoints | What's New |
|------------|-----------|------------|
| **auth.js** | POST `/register`, `/login`, `/logout`, GET `/me` | — |
| **screentime.js** | CRUD entries, POST `/upload` (CSV) | ⭐ Auto-flags entries matching user's distraction list on import |
| **distracting.js** ⭐NEW | GET/POST/DELETE `/api/distracting-apps` | ⭐ Manage per-user distraction list; POST `/detect` receives browser tab data and auto-logs if distracting |
| **tasks.js** ⭐NEW | CRUD `/api/tasks`, GET `/api/tasks/:id/impact` | ⭐ Track tasks, calculate distraction impact (how much work could've been done) |
| **analytics.js** | GET `/dashboard`, `/trends`, `/categories`, `/app-usage` | ⭐ Distraction report: time wasted summary, top distracting apps with percentages |
| **alerts.js** | CRUD alerts, GET `/check` | ⭐ Auto-triggers when distracting app usage exceeds threshold |
| **settings.js** | GET/PUT settings | — |
| **reports.js** | POST `/generate`, GET `/list`, `/download/:id` | ⭐ Per-user reports only (userId filter) |
| **attention.js** | GET `/score` | — |
| **opportunity.js** | GET `/cost` | ⭐ Enhanced suggestions: books, courses, earnings, exercise, task completion estimates |

### Backend — Utils (`server/utils/`)
- **attentionScore.js** — Rule-based scoring (distraction ratio, app switches, notification frequency)
- **opportunityCost.js** — Distraction mins × hourly rate + alternative activity suggestions
- **distractionMatcher.js** ⭐NEW — Matches screen-time entries against user's distraction list (fuzzy name matching + URL matching)
- **taskImpact.js** ⭐NEW — Given distraction time during a task's timeframe, calculates: completion % lost, time remaining if undistracted
- **seedData.js** — Sample data including sample distraction list
- **pdfGenerator.js** — Report builder, now includes distraction summary section

### Backend — Sample Data
**`server/data/sample-screentime.json`** — 30-day dataset with apps: Instagram, YouTube, Chrome, Slack, VS Code, Twitter, Reddit, WhatsApp, Spotify

